50. Construct a PHP script to lower-case and upper-case, all elements in an array.
<?php
$fruits = ["Apple", "Banana", "Orange", "Mango"];
// Convert all elements to lowercase
$lowercase = array_map('strtolower', $fruits);
// Convert all elements to uppercase
$uppercase = array_map('strtoupper', $fruits);
// Print results
echo "Lowercase:\n";
print_r($lowercase);
echo "\nUppercase:\n";
print_r($uppercase);
?>

OUTPUT
Lowercase:
Array
(
    [0] => apple
    [1] => banana
    [2] => orange
    [3] => mango
)

Uppercase:
Array
(
    [0] => APPLE
    [1] => BANANA
    [2] => ORANGE
    [3] => MANGO
)
